subSubSection.paragraph:
Dorsal cirri of median segments kidney-shaped, wider than long (
Fig. 8F–I
). Dorsal cirrophores distally enlarged. Neuropodium with supra-acicular lobes longer than subacicular lobes, with 25–30 chaetae. Dorsal and ventral chaetae similar within single fascicle. Rostrum of chaetal shaft symmetrical, with single short main tooth both sides (
Fig. 37B
). Ventral cirri oval with rounded to weakly pointed ends, longer than neuropodia (
Fig. 8G,I
). Pygidial cirri cylindrical, with rounded ends, 2–3 times as long as wide (
Fig. 6D
). Pygidial papilla present.
